
                                            McLeod was admitted into hospital after telling his wife that he was not feeling well.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Former South African referee Ian McLeod has died on Thursday night, the South African Football Association (Safa) said. McLeod was admitted to hospital last week after telling his wife that he was not feeling well. He was the first South African to referee at a Fifa World Cup tournament, when he officiated in the 1998 global showpiece in France. He was involved in changing the refereeing structures at Safa at the time of his death.     